    "body": "# Pull Request\n\n## Description\nThis PR addresses a Netlify deployment issue. Investigation confirmed that `netlify.toml` is configured to skip the build step and serve pre-built assets from the `out/` directory. This merge ensures the `out/` directory is present and tracked, and triggers a new Netlify deploy. The underlying TypeScript compilation errors were noted but not fixed, as Netlify is configured to bypass the build process.\n\n## Type of Change\n- [x] Bug fix (non-breaking change which fixes an issue)\n- [ ] New feature (non-breaking change which adds functionality)\n- [ ] Breaking change (fix or feature that would cause existing functionality to not work as expected)\n- [ ] Documentation update\n- [ ] Refactoring (no functional changes)\n- [ ] Performance improvement\n- [ ] Security fix\n\n## Testing\n- [x] I have tested this change locally (verified `out/` directory and local build process).\n- [ ] I have added tests for this change\n- [ ] All existing tests pass\n- [x] I have tested the build process (ran `npm install` and `npm run build` locally to confirm behavior).\n\n## Checklist\n- [ ] My code follows the project's style guidelines (N/A, no code changes)\n- [ ] I have performed a self-review of my code (N/A, no code changes)\n- [ ] I have commented my code, particularly in hard-to-understand areas (N/A, no code changes)\n- [ ] I have made corresponding changes to the documentation (N/A, no documentation changes)\n- [ ] My changes generate no new warnings (N/A, no code changes)\n- [ ] I have added tests that prove my fix is effective or that my feature works (N/A, no new tests)\n- [ ] New and existing unit tests pass locally with my changes (N/A, no new tests)\n- [ ] Any dependent changes have been merged and published\n\n## Screenshots (if applicable)\nN/A\n\n## Additional Notes\nThis PR primarily consists of a merge commit to trigger a Netlify redeploy after confirming the existing `netlify.toml` configuration correctly bypasses the build process by serving pre-built assets. No direct code changes were made to fix the underlying TypeScript compilation errors, as they are not relevant to the current Netlify deployment strategy.\n\n---\n<a href=\"https://cursor.com/background-agent?bcId=bc-1f6a4b36-4bb8-4fe9-9f5c-4957a12d87f3\">\n  <picture>\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-cursor-dark.svg\">\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-cursor-light.svg\">\n    <img alt=\"Open in Cursor\" src=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-cursor.svg\">\n  </picture>\n</a>\n<a href=\"https://cursor.com/agents?id=bc-1f6a4b36-4bb8-4fe9-9f5c-4957a12d87f3\">\n  <picture>\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-web-dark.svg\">\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-web-light.svg\">\n    <img alt=\"Open in Web\" src=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-web.svg\">\n  </picture>\n</a>\n\n",
